               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 3ra-126va)
 -
                     Discourse of St Athanasius on death (fols. 3ra-7rb)
 - Maṣḥaf za-wäḍʾat
                     ʾǝm-ʾIyarusalem “Book that Came from Jerusalem” (fols. 10va-18ra)
 - Lǝfāfa
                     ṣǝdq “Bandlet of Righteousness” (fols. 18ra-21va)
 - Mangada samāy “Journey
                     to Heaven” (fols. 21va-22rb)
 - Introduction (fols. 22ra-24vb)
 -
                     Antiphons (kǝśtat, ʾaryām, ʾabun) (fols. 29rb-va, 47ra-rb, 51va—52ra, 53rb-vb,
                     59vb, 61va-vb, 125ra-126va)
 - Homily by St Jacob of Sarug for the funeral
                     of priests and deacons (fols. 69ra-72ra)
 - Homily by ʾabbā Salāmā,
                     Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols. 87ra-91rb)
 II) Ṣalota śǝryätä ḫaṭiʾat
                     “Prayer of Absolution of Sins” (fols. 119va-124vb), (cp. EMML 427(9))
                     
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
