                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre but regular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (luminous vivid scarlet)</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11077Zadengel">Za-Dǝngǝl</persName> is
                        mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#9vb">9vb</locus>. He is attested
                        as the scribe also in a few other Ms.: MY-019, AQG-002, MR-040,
                           AGM-001.<date>First half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ካ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ካሕን፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#25vb">25vb</locus>, 26ra, 28ra)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ሕ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#25vb">25vb</locus>, 26ra, 32rb)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ዲ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡ </expan> (<locus target="#28ra">28ra</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ፍ፡</abbr> for <expan>ፍቱሐ፡ ወንጹሐ፡ ይረስዮ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ በድን፡ </expan>
                                 (<locus target="#38ra">38ra-</locus>va)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; name of the
                           scribe; two groups of lines in the incipit page of Text I, alternating
                           with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the text; names of
                           Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 30vb, 31ra, 32vb); abbreviations;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some
                           other words, e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols. 4ra, 5rb,), wa-tǝbl (e.g.,
                           fols. 35ra, 42rb), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 25vb, 31vb), kǝśtat (e.g., fols.
                           29rb, 47ra), qǝdmä wangle (e.g., fols. 31rb, 33ra), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (fol. 30vb),
                           wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fols. 31va, 33rb).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Angular.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
