                              ለይኩን፡ &lt;...&gt;፡ ቃሎሙ፡ ለሐዋርያት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note mentions Walda Dāwit, who’s baptismal name is Walda
                              Kidos, as the donor. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#126v">f. 126v</locus>
                           <desc>: Record concerning a dispute (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in a crude hand in a pencil and mentions names
                              fitawrari Lämläm, qes Gabra Ṣādǝq and qes Gabra ʾAb. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tamallas-sign indicating the place where the omission,
                           written in the upper margin, belongs: <locus target="#14vb">14vb</locus>.
 - The scribe used compressed script on <locus target="#29rb">29rb-</locus>va, 47ra-rb, 51va—52ra, 53rb-vb, 59vb,
                           61va-vb, 125ra-126va.
 - Corrections written interlineally: e.g.,
                              <locus target="#26ra">26ra</locus>, 35vb, 43ra.
 - Chains of black
                           and red dots as text dividers: e.g., <locus target="#26rb">26rb</locus>,
                           124vb, 126vb.
 - Pen trial on <locus target="#127r">127r</locus>.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Notes in the upper margins written in pen, in
                              black and green inks, referring to the content of the Ms.: fols. 8v,
                              10v, 18r, 22r, 26r, 36v, 37v, 41r, 44r, 49r, 52v, 53v, 58v, 60v, 62v,
                              66r, 67v, 69r, 78v, 83r, 87r, 90r, 91r, 97r, 101r, 114r, 116v, 118r-v,
                              119v. - Coloured threads have been inserted in the upper and outer
                              margins: fols. 8, 37, 69, 83, 87, 91, 116.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
